text: Agdistis karakalensis is a moth in the family Pterophoridae. It is known from Iran, Turkmenistan and Tajikistan.A new species, a new synonym, and new distribution records in the genus Agdistis Hübner, 1825 from Iran (Pterophoridae: Agdistinae) ==References== ==External links== *Новые виды молевидных чешуекрылых (Lepidoptera: Tineidae, Incurvariidae, Brachodidae, Pterophoridae) фауны СССР Category:Moths described in 1990 Category:Agdistinae Category:Moths of the Middle East
title: Agdistis karakalensis
